      "writtenOn": "2018-08-15T14:11:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is something we should simply not do, namely package the whole Go sdk in the docker image. Go is a compiled language. It also limits what we can include in pathkit_aggregator.go because we would have to package the dependencies as we.\n\nHow about:\n- remove the inclusion of Go in the Docker image (that also makes that cleaner) \n- Add another (very simple) Dockerfile that derives from the first and adds the test_pathkit.sh script and the pathkit_aggregator executable\n- Instead of \u0027go run ...\u0027 call the executable in the script\n- For local testing simply inject the script and executable into into the first Docker image",
