      "writtenOn": "2018-08-15T14:11:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "pngBytes contains an image encoded as a PNG. That means you are not hashing the pixels but the encoding with metadata etc.\nIMO, it would also be a good idea (admittedly a bit overcautious) to make sure pngBytes is really a valid PNG file. \nHow about this: \n\n- decode the image in pngBytes which will give you an instance of image.Image that can be converted to a probably *image.NRGBA or *image.RGBA \n- then hash img.Pix \n\nThis is what dm does internally. That way you are guaranteed that the image is decodable by Gold and I think the hash is also going to be more stable for the same image.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 242,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 242,
        "endChar": 43
      },
